==English==
===Expression===
'''to have another think coming'''

====Variant form====
'''to have another thing coming'''

#To be deluded, to be mistaken.

====Usage notes====
*This expression is used only in phrases of the form ''If X thinks that Y, he/she has another think coming!''
*It is usually used in the present tense.
*The form ''to have another thing coming'' is often seen, and arises from hearing the /k/ of ''think'' blended with the /k/ of ''coming'', making ''think'' sound like ''thing''.